ZH: 我们应该对别人正眼相待。
EN: We should treat others with respect.

ZH: 他正眼都不看我一眼。
EN: He didn't even look at me.

ZH: 在写作业的时候，我总是正眼看书。
EN: When doing homework, I always read the books carefully.

ZH: 老师在朗读时，我们都应该正眼看着他。
EN: When the teacher is reading aloud, we should all look at him attentively.

ZH: 做正眼生意是成功的关键。
EN: Doing honest business is the key to success.

ZH: 在正眼对待他人时，我们能建立更好的关系。
EN: By treating others with respect, we can build better relationships. 

ZH: 你能不能正眼看着我回答问题？
EN: Can you please look at me directly when answering the question?

ZH: 他一直用正眼看着我，让我感到很不自在。
EN: He kept staring at me, which made me feel uncomfortable.

ZH: 我们要以正眼对待每一个人，无论他们的背景如何。
EN: We should treat everyone with respect, regardless of their background.

ZH: 在面试时，我们应该正眼看着面试官，表现出自信的态度。
EN: During an interview, we should make eye contact with the interviewer and show confidence.

ZH: 当你与别人交谈时，记得正眼看着他们，这样会更有亲和力。
EN: When talking to someone, remember to look them in the eye, it makes you more approachable.

ZH: 当有人向你请教问题时，你应该正眼回答，而不是漫不经心。
EN: When someone asks you a question, you should answer with attention and not dismissively.

ZH: 作为一个领导者，你要正眼看待团队中的每个人，给予他们足够的尊重。
EN: As a leader, you need to look at each member of your team with respect and give them enough recognition.

ZH: 当在公共场合交谈时，我们应该正眼看着对方，以示尊重。
EN: When having a conversation in a public setting, we should look at the other person directly to show respect.

ZH: 父母教育孩子时，应该以正眼对待，以树立良好的榜样。
EN: Parents should treat their children with respect and set a good example.

ZH: 我们要学会用正眼看待自己的失败，从中吸取经验教训。
EN: We should learn to view our failures with a positive mindset and learn from them.

ZH: 在会议上，我们要用正眼看着发言的人，表示尊重。
EN: During a meeting, we should look at the person speaking to show respect.

ZH: 在争论时，我们要正眼看着对方，保持良好的沟通态度。
EN: During an argument, we should look at the other person to maintain good communication.

ZH: 为了理解对方的观点，我们应该用正眼看着他们，并积极倾听。
EN: To understand someone's perspective, we should look at them directly and actively listen.

ZH: 他发火时，我避免与他正眼相对，以免引起争吵。
EN: When he gets angry, I avoid making eye contact with him to prevent an argument.

ZH: 请在提问时正眼看着我，这样我能更好地回答。
EN: Please look at me directly when asking a question, so that I can answer better.
